  "text": "Organizations with a sharp LO encourage its members and employees to question existing organizational norms that guide their activities related to processing market information and organizational actions (Sinkula, 1994; Sinkula et al., 1997) . This strategic orientation is associated with the innovativeness of organizations and, consequently, organizational performance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) and the quality of relationships that companies develop with their buyers [CITATION_3] .",
